Document: NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationmeshsourcegeometrydata2d.rst
Summary: Stores geometry data for NavigationMesh generation in 2D.

NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

This class stores geometry data for NavigationMesh generation in 2D. It allows you to define obstacles and walkable areas for navigation purposes.

This class is primarily used internally by the NavigationServer2D to generate navigation meshes. You typically don't need to interact with it directly unless you are implementing custom navigation generation logic.

Properties:

*   `geometry_data` (Array[Vector3]): An array of vertices that define the geometry. These vertices are expected to be in a format suitable for triangulation.

Methods:

*   `add_mesh(mesh: Mesh, transform: Transform2D, color: Color)`: Adds a Mesh resource to the geometry data. The mesh will be transformed by the given transform and can be assigned a specific color.
*   `add_polygon(polygon: PackedVector2Array, color: Color)`: Adds a polygon defined by a list of 2D vertices to the geometry data. The polygon will be assigned the specified color.
*   `clear()`: Clears all geometry data stored in this object.

Key Rule: The `geometry_data` property stores vertices in a format that is ready for triangulation. Ensure that any custom geometry you add is properly formatted.
