Document: NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationmeshsourcegeometrydata2d.rst
Summary: Provides methods for managing 2D navigation mesh source geometry data, including adding, retrieving, and clearing obstruction and traversable outlines, as well as projected obstructions.

Method: add_obstruction_outline(shape_outline: PackedVector2Array)
Adds the outline points of a shape as an obstructed area.

Method: add_projected_obstruction(vertices: PackedVector2Array, carve: bool)
Adds a projected obstruction shape. If `carve` is true, the carved shape will not be affected by additional offsets (e.g., agent radius) during navigation mesh baking.

Method: add_traversable_outline(shape_outline: PackedVector2Array)
Adds the outline points of a shape as a traversable area.

Method: append_obstruction_outlines(obstruction_outlines: Array[PackedVector2Array])
Appends another array of obstruction outlines to the existing ones.

Method: append_traversable_outlines(traversable_outlines: Array[PackedVector2Array])
Appends another array of traversable outlines to the existing ones.

Method: clear()
Clears all internal geometry data.

Method: clear_projected_obstructions()
Clears all projected obstructions.

Method: get_bounds() → Rect2
Returns an axis-aligned bounding box encompassing all stored geometry data. The bounds are cached and updated only when geometry changes.

Method: get_obstruction_outlines() → Array[PackedVector2Array]
Returns all stored obstruction area outlines.

Method: get_projected_obstructions() → Array
Returns the projected obstructions. Each element in the array is a dictionary with "vertices" (PackedFloat32Array) and "carve" (bool) keys.

Method: get_traversable_outlines() → Array[PackedVector2Array]
Returns all stored traversable area outlines.

Method: has_data() → bool
Returns true if any source geometry data has been parsed.

Method: merge(other_geometry: NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D)
Adds the geometry data from another NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D instance to this one.

Method: set_obstruction_outlines(obstruction_outlines: Array[PackedVector2Array])
Sets all obstruction area outlines, replacing any existing data.

Method: set_projected_obstructions(projected_obstructions: Array)
Sets the projected obstructions. The input is an Array of Dictionaries, where each dictionary must contain "vertices" (PackedFloat32Array) and "carve" (bool).

Method: set_traversable_outlines(traversable_outlines: Array[PackedVector2Array])
Sets all traversable area outlines, replacing any existing data.